    <h4 class="text-info">ENTRY FORMALITIES & INFORMATION FOR SIKKIM</h4>
    <b>Travelling By Air</b>
    <p class="row-margin-bottom-20">
        You Can Fly Directly To Bagdogra Airport In North Bengal From Delhi, Kolkotta And Guwahati & Bhutan. All Flights Feature Business Class And Amenities Of International Standards. Sikkim Tourism Operates Daily Five Seater Helicopter Service Between Gangtok & Bagdogra Connecting All Civil Filghts, Very Soon Sikkim Will Have Its Own Airport At East Sikkim Pakyong.
    </p>
    <b>Travelling By Road</b>
    <p class="row-margin-bottom-20">
        All Visitors Entering Sikkim By Land Must Use No Other Entry Points Other Than (1) Kakarbhitta (2) Phunstholling (3) Siliguri / New Jalpaiguri Railway Station, Bagdogra Airport (4) Darjeeling (5) Kalimpong.
    </p>
    <b>Travelling By Train</b>
    <p>
        All Visitors Entering Sikkim By Train The Two Closet Railway Stations Are Siliguri & New Jalpaiguri Connecting Kolkotta, Guwahati, Lucknow And Other Important Cities In India.
    </p>
